-- =============================================================================
-- §23. IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
-- =============================================================================
--
-- PlanningDashboard: most complex page — 8 model fields, 15+ Msg variants.
--   HITL timeout policy is an open question (see §13).
-- Prajna: circuit_state machine must be kept in sync with Rust health_orchestra.rs.
-- ZenohMesh: lifecycle transitions MUST mirror Rust zenoh_telemetry.rs state machine.
-- Podman: StartContainer/StopContainer MUST delegate to IgnitionDaemon (SC-ARCH-SPLIT-001).
--   Gleam page is display-only; no subprocess or CLI invocation from Lustre update().

-- =============================================================================
-- §24. DESIGN PRINCIPLES & PATTERNS
-- =============================================================================
--
-- MVU purity: update() is a pure function — all effects returned as Effect values.
-- Fail-visible: error states are always rendered, never silently swallowed.
-- Triple mandate: feature = Lustre + Wisp + TUI; 2/3 = incomplete.
-- Muda: unused imports and dead functions removed before commit (SC-MUDA-001).
-- Fractal separation: Gleam = UI/types/testing, Rust = orchestration (SC-ARCH-SPLIT).
-- OTel-first: every state transition emits a span; observability is not optional.

-- =============================================================================
-- §25. ANTI-PATTERNS
-- =============================================================================
--
-- Client JS in Lustre pages (Lustre is SSR — no JS bundles).
-- Orchestration logic (container start/stop) inside Gleam update().
-- Per-page type definitions duplicating ui/domain.gleam.
-- Wildcard catch-all in update() suppressing unhandled Msg variants.
-- Suppressed compile warnings treated as acceptable (each is a MUDA violation).
-- HTTP polling from TUI instead of Zenoh subscription (ZMOF mandate violated).
-- Guardian-required actions auto-approved without HITL check.

-- =============================================================================
-- §26. SESSION JOURNAL TEMPLATE (SC-JOURNAL, 13 sections)
-- =============================================================================
--
-- 1. Scope & Trigger    — which pages/rules changed and why
-- 2. Pre-State          — compile status, test count, warning count before
-- 3. Execution Detail   — exact files edited, Msg variants added/removed
-- 4. RCA                — root cause if bug fix (5-Why)
-- 5. Fix Taxonomy       — category: new-page | new-msg | invariant-fix | muda
-- 6. Patterns/Anti-Patterns — what worked, what to avoid
-- 7. Verification Matrix — gleam build clean? gleam test pass? triple-interface?
-- 8. Files Modified     — absolute paths
-- 9. Architecture       — fractal layer impact, Rust bridge changes if any
-- 10. Remaining Gaps    — open questions still unresolved, missing TUI views
-- 11. Metrics           — test count delta, ITQS score, warning count
-- 12. STAMP Alignment   — which SC-*/AOR-* satisfied by this session
-- 13. Conclusion        — ready for merge? Guardian approval needed?

