-- =============================================================================
-- §29. ZENOH + MCP INTEGRATION STATUS (2026-04-05)
-- =============================================================================
--
-- Zenoh FFI status:
--   Path 1 (Elixir/Mix context): FUNCTIONAL — Rustler NIF loaded via Indrajaal.Native.Zenoh
--   Path 2 (Standalone gleam run): DEGRADED — NIF requires Elixir module context
--   Remediation: Run cepaf_gleam HTTP server as supervised child of Elixir OTP app
--
-- MoZ Client (moz/client.gleam):
--   Protocol: JSON-RPC 2.0 over Zenoh pub/sub
--   Request topic: indrajaal/l4/ignition/mcp/req/{method}/{request_id}
--   Response topic: indrajaal/l4/ignition/mcp/res/{request_id}
--   Active tools: launch, restart, drain (+ status, preflight, rca, planning_status, planning_add)
--   Circuit breaker: 5 failures → open, 30s → half_open
--
-- Rust MCP Bridge (mcp_bridge.rs):
--   8 tools registered and handled
--   Heartbeat: every 1000ms to indrajaal/l4/ignition/{node_id}/heartbeat
--   Catalog: republished every heartbeat cycle
--
-- Known limitation: In standalone gleam run mode, Zenoh NIF is not available.
-- The canonical deployment is cepaf_gleam Wisp server running as a child process
-- within the Elixir OTP application, where Zenoh NIF is loaded by Rustler.
-- SC-ZENOH-001 is satisfied in this deployment mode.
